{{italic title}} [[File:Dance of Salome 88.jpg|thumb|right|''Dance of Salome'', mixed media on paper, 115 X 79 cm (45 X 31 inches), 1988]] '''''The Dance of Salomé''''' is the title of a series of 160 works consisting of 85 [[painting]]s and 75 [[drawing]]s created by [[Nabil Kanso]] in 1988 and 1995.<ref>[http://nabilkanso.com/SALOME.html ''The Dance of Salome'']</ref> It is based on biblical and literary works with particular reference to [[Oscar Wilde]]’s [[Salome (play)|drama]] (1893) and [[Richard Strauss]]’s [[Salome (opera)|opera]] (1905). The primary subject of all the works in the series is [[Salome|Salomé]] who is depicted in a sequence of scenes reflecting various nuances of perception in distinctive dance movement.<ref>[http://apocalypsepainting.com/interview.html Nabil Kanso: “Dance of Salome”]</ref>
